    <h2>Research</h2>
    Household robots planning long-horizon behavior, such as heating up takeouts and cleaning the kitchen counter, must be able to <b>plan quickly and execute robustly</b> in <b>semantically rich, geometrically complex environments</b>. I'm working on the following problems in the field of robotic learning and Task and Motion Planning (TAMP):
    <ul>
      <li> Learn to plan with information provided by pre-trained vision-language models. </li>
      <li> Learn to manipulate objects that are partially observable using a mobile robot. </li>
      <li> Learn to solve continuous constraint satisfaction problems (e.g. packing without collisions). </li>
      <li> Learn to predict task plan feasibility from images of worlds with articulated and movable obstacles. </li>
      <li> Hierarchical planning and replanning in partially observable TAMP problems. </li>
    </ul>

